WEBVTT

﻿1
00:00:01.356 --> 00:00:02.773
<i>What does Tim wanna show us?</i>

2
00:00:02.774 --> 00:00:04.650
He'll kill me if
I ruin the surprise.

3
00:00:04.651 --> 00:00:05.776
It's not a waffle truck.

4
00:00:05.777 --> 00:00:07.486
- I asked.
- Oh.

5
00:00:07.487 --> 00:00:08.987
Welcome.

6
00:00:08.988 --> 00:00:11.615
Wanted you guys be
the first to see my new office.

7
00:00:11.616 --> 00:00:13.325
Look. if I'm gonna be
a more "out on the street"

8
00:00:13.326 --> 00:00:15.244
watch commander. I need
to take my office with me.

9
00:00:15.245 --> 00:00:17.913
Is this the new
interceptor utility vehicle?

10
00:00:17.914 --> 00:00:22.292
It is. 700 horsepower.
8.000-pound towing capacity.

11
00:00:22.293 --> 00:00:25.254
Level 4 ballistic door panels.
dark mode.

12
00:00:25.255 --> 00:00:28.173
and 270-degree monitoring
to analyze moving objects

13
00:00:28.174 --> 00:00:29.466
for potential threat levels.

14
00:00:29.467 --> 00:00:31.009
He calls it a Super Shop.

15
00:00:31.010 --> 00:00:32.636
That's a working title.

16
00:00:32.637 --> 00:00:36.181
You see. we got hats
and bats. infrared camera.

17
00:00:36.182 --> 00:00:37.432
breaching tools.

18
00:00:37.433 --> 00:00:38.684
Oh. yeah.

19
00:00:38.685 --> 00:00:40.978
- Two 32-inch screens.
- Whoo.

20
00:00:40.979 --> 00:00:42.354
Wow.

21
00:00:42.355 --> 00:00:43.605
Can I be watch commander?

22
00:00:43.606 --> 00:00:45.315
No. but you are
riding with me today.

23
00:00:45.316 --> 00:00:47.276
- Yes.
- Oh. hey. show them Droney.

24
00:00:47.277 --> 00:00:49.403
- Oh. yeah.
Check this out.

25
00:00:56.786 --> 00:00:57.828
Isn't he cute?

26
00:00:57.829 --> 00:00:59.663
- She.
- Really?

27
00:00:59.664 --> 00:01:01.039
- Yeah.
- Oh.

28
00:01:01.040 --> 00:01:02.040
Super Shop makes
the Batmobile look

29
00:01:02.041 --> 00:01:03.542
like a kiddie toy.

30
00:01:03.543 --> 00:01:06.628
And I can control it all
right here from my phone.

31
00:01:07.797 --> 00:01:09.506
See?

32
00:01:11.259 --> 00:01:13.010
Damn it.

33
00:01:13.011 --> 00:01:15.762
Whoa. whoa. damn it.

34
00:01:15.763 --> 00:01:17.681
<i>Playing Tim's Pump Up Jams.</i>

35
00:01:18.683 --> 00:01:21.935
Stop. stop. stop.

36
00:01:23.000 --> 00:01:29.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

37
00:01:30.194 --> 00:01:31.903
It's not gonna be
as easy as you think.

38
00:01:31.904 --> 00:01:34.489
Based on this morning's
demonstration. I'm well aware.

39
00:01:34.490 --> 00:01:36.199
It's not just that you're taking

40
00:01:36.200 --> 00:01:37.909
the watch commander duties
on patrol.

41
00:01:37.910 --> 00:01:41.788
You're also exposing yourself
to chain-of-command confusion

42
00:01:41.789 --> 00:01:44.124
when you land at a scene.
even if you stay in the SUV.

43
00:01:44.125 --> 00:01:45.876
Super Shop.

44
00:01:45.877 --> 00:01:47.337
It's a working name.

45
00:01:52.800 --> 00:01:53.925
Good morning.

46
00:01:53.926 --> 00:01:55.385
- Good morning.
- Good morning.

47
00:01:55.386 --> 00:01:57.012
All right. listen up.
we're gonna do things

48
00:01:57.013 --> 00:01:58.680
a little different today.

49
00:01:58.681 --> 00:02:00.932
There'll be two supervisors
out on the street.

50
00:02:00.933 --> 00:02:03.644
Sergeant Chen and myself.

51
00:02:04.729 --> 00:02:06.396
I know. I know.

52
00:02:06.397 --> 00:02:08.189
No one wants the boss
showing up to their calls.

53
00:02:08.190 --> 00:02:09.775
second-guessing
their every move.

54
00:02:09.776 --> 00:02:12.778
That is not my intention. okay?
Nothing has to change.

55
00:02:12.779 --> 00:02:14.237
I just put wheels on my office.

56
00:02:14.238 --> 00:02:15.530
And while we work
out the details.

57
00:02:15.531 --> 00:02:17.699
Officer Nolan will be
riding with me to help

58
00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:19.451
facilitate the transition.

59
00:02:19.452 --> 00:02:21.036
Any questions?

60
00:02:21.037 --> 00:02:22.497
Can I pick the playlist?

61
00:02:23.915 --> 00:02:25.749
It's a dumb question.

62
00:02:25.750 --> 00:02:28.251
All right. second order
of business. Officer Juarez

63
00:02:28.252 --> 00:02:29.419
will be on temporary
duty assignment

64
00:02:29.420 --> 00:02:31.338
with the Detectives Bureau.

65
00:02:31.339 --> 00:02:32.422
Did you choose your focus?

66
00:02:32.423 --> 00:02:34.466
Yes. Missing Persons.

67
00:02:34.467 --> 00:02:36.134
Oof.

68
00:02:36.135 --> 00:02:38.512
- Are you sure about that?
- Yeah.

69
00:02:38.513 --> 00:02:40.222
Your call.

70
00:02:40.223 --> 00:02:41.556
All right. I have some
updates from the night shift.

71
00:02:41.557 --> 00:02:44.518
Is Missing Persons
really that bad?

72
00:02:44.519 --> 00:02:46.645
Detective Desmond
has a reputation.

73
00:02:46.646 --> 00:02:48.772
Like a Harper reputation?

74
00:02:48.773 --> 00:02:52.025
No. opposite.

75
00:02:52.026 --> 00:02:54.236
Last day at the DA's office.

76
00:02:54.237 --> 00:02:55.696
Excited?
<i>- I'm relieved.</i>

77
00:02:55.697 --> 00:02:57.489
When the DA had
one foot in retirement.

78
00:02:57.490 --> 00:03:00.075
now that Vivian's DA-elect.
she's gonna have free reign.

79
00:03:00.076 --> 00:03:01.535
Well. none of that will matter

80
00:03:01.536 --> 00:03:03.286
once you quit and open
a private practice in Malibu

81
00:03:03.287 --> 00:03:04.705
with a view of the ocean.

82
00:03:04.706 --> 00:03:07.374
Uh. with that commute.
you'd never see me again.

83
00:03:07.375 --> 00:03:10.627
Well. in my dream.
I also work in Malibu.

84
00:03:10.628 --> 00:03:12.045
<i>I have a robot
helicopter that flies</i>

85
00:03:12.046 --> 00:03:14.089
the kids to school and a pony.

86
00:03:14.090 --> 00:03:15.465
<i>Well. sorry to kill
another one of your dreams.</i>

87
00:03:15.466 --> 00:03:17.259
But I already reached out
to my old landlord.

88
00:03:17.260 --> 00:03:18.802
and the only view
from that office

89
00:03:18.803 --> 00:03:20.846
is the Ethiopian place
on the first floor.

90
00:03:20.847 --> 00:03:22.848
Oh. before you go. make sure
you pass off my cases

91
00:03:22.849 --> 00:03:24.266
to the right prosecutors.

92
00:03:24.267 --> 00:03:25.976
Daniels doesn't touch homicide.

93
00:03:25.977 --> 00:03:27.936
- Give mine to Cosgrove.
He is solid.

94
00:03:27.937 --> 00:03:28.812
That might be an issue.

95
00:03:28.813 --> 00:03:30.147
Cosgrove just quit.

96
00:03:30.148 --> 00:03:32.107
<i>I gotta go.</i>
- Good luck.

97
00:03:32.108 --> 00:03:33.733
Wesley. it's so good to see you.

98
00:03:33.734 --> 00:03:35.360
Yeah. right.

99
00:03:35.361 --> 00:03:37.279
- I'm serious.
No hard feelings on my end.

100
00:03:37.280 --> 00:03:38.321
Yeah. because you destroyed me.

101
00:03:38.322 --> 00:03:39.698
Well. exactly.

102
00:03:39.699 --> 00:03:41.158
I made good on the promise
I made you when you

103
00:03:41.159 --> 00:03:42.659
threw your hat in the ring.
It's nothing personal.

104
00:03:42.660 --> 00:03:45.078
In fact. I agree with you
on a lot of the issues.

105
00:03:45.079 --> 00:03:47.122
And I know that together.
we can take the DA's office

106
00:03:47.123 --> 00:03:48.415
in a positive direction.

107
00:03:48.416 --> 00:03:50.625
- Mm-hmm.
- Mm-hmm.

108
00:03:50.626 --> 00:03:52.335
You're not gonna
fall for that. are you?

109
00:03:52.336 --> 00:03:53.837
No.

110
00:03:53.838 --> 00:03:55.088
I was about to hand in
my resignation letter.

111
00:03:55.089 --> 00:03:56.423
Well. she won't accept it.

112
00:03:56.424 --> 00:03:58.175
With Cosgrove.
Garcia. and Martin

113
00:03:58.176 --> 00:04:00.051
already out. she can't
afford to lose anyone else.

114
00:04:00.052 --> 00:04:02.387
- Martin quit?
- Keyed her car on the way out.

115
00:04:02.388 --> 00:04:04.556
A hero to us all.

116
00:04:04.557 --> 00:04:06.225
Come on.

117
00:04:07.810 --> 00:04:09.895
Hey. sorry about the election.

118
00:04:09.896 --> 00:04:11.271
That should have been
me facing Vivian.

119
00:04:11.272 --> 00:04:13.064
You were handed
a poison chalice.

120
00:04:13.065 --> 00:04:14.900
I drank from it willingly.

121
00:04:14.901 --> 00:04:16.275
How's Logan?

122
00:04:16.276 --> 00:04:17.777
He's good.

123
00:04:17.778 --> 00:04:19.529
He just got another chip.

124
00:04:19.530 --> 00:04:22.115
He's been clean now
almost four months.

125
00:04:22.116 --> 00:04:23.783
That's great.

126
00:04:23.784 --> 00:04:25.368
What about you?

127
00:04:25.369 --> 00:04:26.703
You gonna do the Rothwell
and Pierce thing?

128
00:04:26.704 --> 00:04:28.955
No. I'm...

129
00:04:28.956 --> 00:04:30.123
I'm gonna stay here.

130
00:04:30.124 --> 00:04:31.541
And you should too.

131
00:04:31.542 --> 00:04:33.210
Hmm.

132
00:04:33.211 --> 00:04:34.711
Come on. Wes. you joined this
place to change the culture

133
00:04:34.712 --> 00:04:38.173
from within.
to ensure that justice.

134
00:04:38.174 --> 00:04:41.134
not punishment. was our
paramount virtue. remember?

135
00:04:41.135 --> 00:04:43.178
It's a very
inspirational message

136
00:04:43.179 --> 00:04:45.388
that just lost by 23 points.

137
00:04:45.389 --> 00:04:47.140
Look. Vivian ran
on tough on crime.

138
00:04:47.141 --> 00:04:48.725
She's gonna deliver.

139
00:04:48.726 --> 00:04:51.144
Yeah. which is why the city
needs people like us here

140
00:04:51.145 --> 00:04:52.687
now more than ever.

141
00:04:52.688 --> 00:04:54.731
Look. we still can
make a difference.

142
00:04:54.732 --> 00:04:56.358
- Sean.
- You're here already.

143
00:04:56.359 --> 00:04:58.151
Let's work together.
one last time.

144
00:04:58.152 --> 00:05:00.153
If at the end of the day.
you still wanna quit.

145
00:05:00.154 --> 00:05:02.113
I won't stay in your way.

146
00:05:02.114 --> 00:05:05.617
This job is where
ambition goes to die.

147
00:05:05.618 --> 00:05:06.660
Wait. what?

148
00:05:06.661 --> 00:05:07.744
Missing Persons.

149
00:05:07.745 --> 00:05:09.704
It's not a real department.

150
00:05:09.705 --> 00:05:12.791
It's a halfway house for cases
on the way to real departments.

151
00:05:12.792 --> 00:05:15.377
That's a lot of reports
for a fake department.

152
00:05:15.378 --> 00:05:17.546
90% of these cases
will solve themselves.

153
00:05:17.547 --> 00:05:19.631
Teenager just needed
to blow off steam.

154
00:05:19.632 --> 00:05:22.467
A wife went on a bender.
came home when she sobered up.

155
00:05:22.468 --> 00:05:24.302
Kid fell asleep
playing hide-and-seek.

156
00:05:24.303 --> 00:05:25.887
I've been on patrol
for three years.

157
00:05:25.888 --> 00:05:28.431
I know most missing persons
reports go nowhere.

158
00:05:28.432 --> 00:05:31.142
but there are people
in this stack

159
00:05:31.143 --> 00:05:33.019
who are victims of real crimes.

160
00:05:33.020 --> 00:05:34.312
Crimes with their
own departments.

161
00:05:34.313 --> 00:05:36.940
like Trafficking or Homicide.

162
00:05:36.941 --> 00:05:38.233
Sorry to interrupt.

163
00:05:38.234 --> 00:05:40.402
Homicide wants the McGrath case.

164
00:05:40.403 --> 00:05:42.112
Fisherman found the body.

165
00:05:42.113 --> 00:05:44.073
Looks like murder.
- Rest in peace.

166
00:05:46.617 --> 00:05:49.411
Okay. obviously.
you know the job

167
00:05:49.412 --> 00:05:51.705
way better than I do.
but wouldn't hurt

168
00:05:51.706 --> 00:05:53.248
to look through the case files.

169
00:05:53.249 --> 00:05:55.834
see if there's anyone
we can help?

170
00:05:55.835 --> 00:05:56.794
Knock yourself out.

171
00:06:03.175 --> 00:06:05.844
This thing drives
like a dream...

172
00:06:05.845 --> 00:06:07.804
and these seats.

173
00:06:07.805 --> 00:06:10.390
Ten minutes in a regular shop.
my ass is barking.

174
00:06:10.391 --> 00:06:12.058
Well. don't get used to it.

175
00:06:12.059 --> 00:06:13.852
You're just here while
I work out the kinks.

176
00:06:13.853 --> 00:06:15.478
Once Penn is back from training.

177
00:06:15.479 --> 00:06:17.522
you're back in the shop.
and I'm on my own.

178
00:06:17.523 --> 00:06:19.774
<i>I have a 4-15 at
5th and Western.</i>

179
00:06:19.775 --> 00:06:22.944
<i>RP reports two shirtless men
circling each other.</i>

180
00:06:22.945 --> 00:06:24.237
7-Adam-100 two blocks away.

181
00:06:24.238 --> 00:06:25.572
Show us responding.

182
00:06:25.573 --> 00:06:26.948
Are you sure?

183
00:06:26.949 --> 00:06:29.200
Sounds like your basic
alcohol-fueled slugfest.

184
00:06:29.201 --> 00:06:30.785
Yeah. I have to test
response times on even

185
00:06:30.786 --> 00:06:32.495
the most basic of calls.

186
00:06:34.498 --> 00:06:36.124
Captain's calling.

187
00:06:36.125 --> 00:06:37.125
Bradford.

188
00:06:37.126 --> 00:06:38.335
<i>Can you hold?</i>

189
00:06:38.336 --> 00:06:40.128
Yeah. I'll hold.

190
00:06:43.466 --> 00:06:46.927
I'll be right there.
- I got this one.

191
00:06:46.928 --> 00:06:48.803
LAPD. You guys. break it up.

192
00:06:48.804 --> 00:06:50.347
Come on.

193
00:06:50.348 --> 00:06:51.640
<i>Sorry. he was
called into a meeting.</i>

194
00:06:51.641 --> 00:06:53.099
<i>Can you hold just
a minute longer?</i>

195
00:06:53.100 --> 00:06:55.101
<i>Thanks.</i>
- No. I'm out on...

196
00:06:58.648 --> 00:07:00.190
Hey.

197
00:07:02.193 --> 00:07:03.234
Hey. keep your hands
where I can see them.

198
00:07:03.235 --> 00:07:05.570
Just stay right there.

199
00:07:05.571 --> 00:07:07.864
<i>- Sorry to keep you waiting.</i>
- No problem. sir.

200
00:07:07.865 --> 00:07:09.157
<i>We're getting a
lot of complaints</i>

201
00:07:09.158 --> 00:07:11.493
<i>about vagrants in Stoner Park.</i>

202
00:07:11.494 --> 00:07:14.162
I've gotta say. renaming it
would be a strong start.

203
00:07:14.163 --> 00:07:16.623
<i>It's important that people
feel safe in public places.</i>

204
00:07:16.624 --> 00:07:18.208
Couldn't agree more.

205
00:07:18.209 --> 00:07:19.834
I'll have additional units
in the area starting today.

206
00:07:19.835 --> 00:07:21.544
Okay. is that it?

207
00:07:21.545 --> 00:07:23.380
<i>One more thing.
I just wanna say.</i>

208
00:07:23.381 --> 00:07:24.714
<i>your tireless commitment
to justice</i>

209
00:07:24.715 --> 00:07:26.383
<i>and the people of this city...</i>

210
00:07:26.384 --> 00:07:28.343
Thank you. sir.

211
00:07:28.344 --> 00:07:30.762
Hey. hey. hey. hey.

212
00:07:30.763 --> 00:07:31.930
Good job. sir.

213
00:07:31.931 --> 00:07:33.765
You supervised the hell
out of that.

214
00:07:33.766 --> 00:07:35.433
You're still here.

215
00:07:35.434 --> 00:07:37.185
And I think I found
a workable case.

216
00:07:37.186 --> 00:07:40.063
Sadie Bell. 30. was
reported missing last week.

217
00:07:40.064 --> 00:07:41.690
but according to her
best friend. Joe.

218
00:07:41.691 --> 00:07:43.900
Sadie never misses
visitation with her kid

219
00:07:43.901 --> 00:07:46.945
on the first Tuesday
of every month.

220
00:07:46.946 --> 00:07:49.572
Walk with me.

221
00:07:49.573 --> 00:07:51.950
Reporting party's address?

222
00:07:51.951 --> 00:07:53.618
5200 6th Street.

223
00:07:53.619 --> 00:07:54.744
It's a homeless shelter.

224
00:07:54.745 --> 00:07:56.788
Joe is unhoused.
meaning Sadie's unhoused.

225
00:07:56.789 --> 00:07:58.415
Not the most reliable bunch.

226
00:07:58.416 --> 00:08:00.500
On the other hand. sir.
unhoused women

227
00:08:00.501 --> 00:08:03.378
are highly vulnerable to
physical and sexual assaults.

228
00:08:03.379 --> 00:08:05.505
True. and they're also
more likely to be

229
00:08:05.506 --> 00:08:07.424
substance abusers who miss
things like supervised

230
00:08:07.425 --> 00:08:08.842
child visitations.

231
00:08:08.843 --> 00:08:10.343
Oh. I know.

232
00:08:10.344 --> 00:08:11.428
Well. I think it's
worth investigating.

233
00:08:11.429 --> 00:08:13.388
So what's our first step?

234
00:08:13.389 --> 00:08:15.515
Why are you so gung ho.
Officer Juarez?

235
00:08:15.516 --> 00:08:18.227
And don't just say
the indefatigability of youth.

236
00:08:21.022 --> 00:08:24.274
My sister was abducted
when I was a child. sir.

237
00:08:24.275 --> 00:08:28.862
I lived the fear of not knowing
where a loved one is.

238
00:08:28.863 --> 00:08:31.656
Understandable and quite noble.

239
00:08:31.657 --> 00:08:34.284
But I would caution you
that the thousand files

240
00:08:34.285 --> 00:08:36.703
in my office are not
an unending stack

241
00:08:36.704 --> 00:08:38.163
of potential happy endings.

242
00:08:38.164 --> 00:08:40.081
For the subset that are not just

243
00:08:40.082 --> 00:08:43.168
runaways or miscommunications.

244
00:08:43.169 --> 00:08:45.045
the endings are
mostly heartbreaking.

245
00:08:49.050 --> 00:08:50.675
I haven't had a chance
to review the reports.

246
00:08:50.676 --> 00:08:52.427
but it's at the top of my list.

247
00:08:52.428 --> 00:08:54.138
Okay. I appreciate the reminder.

248
00:08:55.931 --> 00:08:57.849
How did Grey make it
look so easy?

249
00:08:57.850 --> 00:08:59.309
Well. the scowl helped.

250
00:08:59.310 --> 00:09:01.603
Yeah. you don't wanna bother
that face

251
00:09:01.604 --> 00:09:03.521
with anything less than
an absolute emergency.

252
00:09:03.522 --> 00:09:05.565
My scowl is legendary.

253
00:09:05.566 --> 00:09:06.983
It was.

254
00:09:06.984 --> 00:09:08.277
But then Lucy moved in.

255
00:09:09.695 --> 00:09:11.196
You know what?

256
00:09:11.197 --> 00:09:13.198
I take it back.

257
00:09:13.199 --> 00:09:15.366
